The excess for each year is the percentage increase above

Every year (2020, 2021, 2022) sees such an increase for the
summer months, but in 2022 it is much more pronounced,
presumably in part because of the availability of the 9-Ticket,
although other effects related to the pandemic and school-
holidays (which are different for each state) likely also play a
role. The effect, measured in the difference in percentage
points between 2021 and 2022, is visualised on the barcharts
Effect of 9-Ticket on transit station activity
based on the Community Mobility Reports by Google
The transit index indicates visitors (or time spent in) transit stations, as compared to January 2020. A higher index does not necessarily
mean more visitors. The transit index base value is 100, indicating that within a 7-day window there is no change from the January 2020
It must be noted that transit stations include public transportation infrastructure such as subway stations, but also highway rest stops,
The data was provided by Google LLC via the Community Mobility reports. It is available between February 2020 and October 2022.
In the summer of 2022, monthly passes for Germany-wide
local and regional transport were available for the
comparatively low price of 9. This figure shows the
estimated effect on transit activity during these summer
months of June, July, and August 2022.
